Program: Great Lives
Title: Max Miller
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00glw45
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 15 Aug 2006
TV critic Garry Bushell proposes Max Miller, one of the highest-paid and most popular comedians of the 20th century. With the help of Roy Hudd, who worked with Miller, he examines the career of the 'cheeky chappie'.